'''Hilde Gudilla Lion''' (1893–1970) was a German Jewish academic and teacher of [[social worker]]s who emigrated to England in 1933, after the [[Nazi seizure of power]]. She founded [[Stoatley Rough School]] for German refugees in 1934 and was its headmistress until 1960.<ref name=5T/><ref name=LHS/>
